HEADWORD: Motherwort
<hw>Moth"er*wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A labiate herb (<spn>Leonurus Cardiaca</spn>), of a
bitter taste, used popularly in medicine; lion's tail.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The mugwort. See <er>Mugwort</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

